# Define the path to the directory containing the images
train_folder = pathlib.Path('../8939740/Birds/train/')
test_folder = pathlib.Path('../8939740/Birds/test/')
valid_folder = pathlib.Path('../8939740/Birds/valid/')

image_count = {}

for species in os.listdir(train_folder):
    species_path = os.path.join(train_folder, species)
    if os.path.isdir(species_path):
        image_count[species] = len(os.listdir(species_path))

# sort the dict to list of 3 top classes
top3_classes = sorted(image_count, key=image_count.get, reverse=True)[:3]

#print the top 3 classes and number of images in each class
print("Top 3 classes and number of images in each class:")
for i in top3_classes:
    print(i, image_count[i])

# Move images from train folder to top3_classes folders
for species in top3_classes:
    source_path = os.path.join(train_folder, species)
    destination_path = os.path.join('../8939740/Birds/train/', species)
    shutil.move(source_path, destination_path)

# Move images from test folder to top3_classes folders
for species in top3_classes:
    source_path = os.path.join(test_folder, species)
    destination_path = os.path.join('../8939740/Birds/test/', species)
    shutil.move(source_path, destination_path)

# Move images from valid folder to top3_classes folders
for species in top3_classes:
    source_path = os.path.join(valid_folder, species)
    destination_path = os.path.join('../8939740/Birds/valid/', species)
    shutil.move(source_path, destination_path)

# Remove unwanted directories
for species in os.listdir(train_folder):
    if species not in top3_classes:
        shutil.rmtree(os.path.join(train_folder, species))

for species in os.listdir(test_folder):
    if species not in top3_classes:
        shutil.rmtree(os.path.join(test_folder, species))

for species in os.listdir(valid_folder):
    if species not in top3_classes:
        shutil.rmtree(os.path.join(valid_folder, species))

# Defining data generator
data_gen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rescale=1.0/255.0,  
    rotation_range=20, 
    width_shift_range=0.2,  
    height_shift_range=0.2, 
    horizontal_flip=True  
)

# Use flow_from_directory to load and preprocess images
batch_size = 32
image_size = (224, 224) 
class_mode = 'categorical'  

data_folder = pathlib.Path("../8939740/Birds/birds.csv")

train_generator = data_gen.flow_from_directory(
    "../8939740/Birds/train/",
    target_size=image_size,
    batch_size=batch_size,
    class_mode=class_mode
)

valid_generator = data_gen.flow_from_directory(
    "../8939740/Birds/valid/",
    target_size=image_size,
    batch_size=batch_size,
    class_mode=class_mode
)

test_generator = data_gen.flow_from_directory(
    "../8939740/Birds/test/",
    target_size=image_size,
    batch_size=batch_size,
    class_mode=class_mode,
    shuffle=False  # Don't shuffle test data
)

In [13]:
# Load the VGG16 model
base_model = VGG16(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(224, 224, 3))

# Freeze the pre-trained weights
for layer in base_model.layers:
    layer.trainable = False

# Adding layers for classification
x = base_model.output
x = layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D()(x)
x = layers.Dense(128, activation='relu')(x)
x = layers.Dropout(0.5)(x)
predictions = layers.Dense(3, activation='softmax')(x)

# Combine the base model and the custom layers
model = Model(inputs=base_model.input, outputs=predictions)

    epochs=10,
    validation_data=valid_generator)

# Calculate confusion matrix, precision, recall, F1-score, precision-recall curve and AUC
y_pred = model.predict(test_generator)
y_pred_classes = np.argmax(y_pred, axis=1)
true_classes = test_generator.classes

# Confusion matrix
cm = confusion_matrix(true_classes, y_pred_classes)
print("Confusion Matrix:\n", cm)

accuracy = np.trace(cm) / float(np.sum(cm))
misclass = 1 - accuracy
print(f'Test Accuracy: {accuracy:.2f}')
print(f'validation_accuracy: {validation_accuracy}')

# Classification Report
print("Classification Report:")
classif_report = classification_report(true_classes, y_pred_classes, target_names=top3_classes)
print(classif_report)
